item.title: Why dont any rsps's have uniqueness they all are exactly like jagex
item.dc:creator: @hadlich4 hadlich4
item.description:
@hadlich4 wrote:

[quote=“Cres, post:20, topic:545683”]Generic intro text to a “317” server nowadays:

Comy my survur has 700+ items, working summoning, d claws, korasi, dungeoneering and dungeoneering items, working highswores, voting system, overpriced donator service, staff of light, accurate combat, legit and active staff who interact with the community, 317, 474, 508, 562 gameframes, loads of customs, tons of minigames, and more!

Yeah, I agree. There’s no server out there that makes me feel like playing actively because I know what it’ll feel like when I’ve achieved everything and gained max wealth. On another note, most of the people who used to play Runescape or RSPS have grown up and only play for short amounts of time (if they decide to play at all). I’ve recently helped out on a server and one of the players contacted me and asked me how to donate. He was 12. Literally. On top of all the problems at user-level, the problem with RSPS themselves is that you can’t really integrate another system into it (or at least not without revising some of the core systems and functionalities in an RSPS and this would only piss people off and scare them from playing.) Like my favorite oldfag Sini said, it’s very hard to find a “fun” concept that you CAN integrate into an RSPS. Most concepts just don’t fit with what we’re given to work with.[/quote]

I agree completely with this age and coding knowledge and the ability to even make something unique has a lot to do with it, i hope once i finish my project and release it that itll bring in a good amount of people.

item.dc:creator: @Elrick Elrick
item.description:
@Elrick wrote:

[quote=“sinisoul, post:8, topic:545683”][quote author=Davidi2 link=topic=664566.msg4442588#msg4442588 date=1407301590]
Hunger games RS was a good example.
[/quote]

I think these mods are better suited for Minecraft.[/quote]
Not to mention this kind of minigame already exists in Runescape already… Fight Pits? The only difference is that it isn’t in a forest.

And I would have to say over the course of RSPS history we’ve seen some pretty awesome ones. PK-Isle always comes to mind when I think of a genuinely unique RSPS. A lot of people have custom bosses and loot tables. I know Arham has been spewing out updates for his server, which I have followed since its release into Beta and is pretty promising.

Overall though, it comes down to a lack of coding. Those who do have knowledge just used RSPS to futher their learning and then moved on, not to mention Sini puts this into perspective:

Why Were RSPS Never Taken Seriously?

It’s not really worth spending my time recreating Run escape when it’s illegal and I can focus my time on something less illegal and put it on my resume

Because ‘coders’ release things they think are “new” and “different” when it’s the same crap.
Ghetto-Online ★ Fully Custom Modern City Environment★Custom Maps/Skills/Content

Also, I want to point something out here.

We’re using Jagex’s cache. Their client, and building servers off of it. Correct? Correct.
And a lot of players are familiar with RuneScape, yes?

So what better way to make a RuneScape Private Server easier to play than to relate it to the game it came from?

You can go ahead and do what ghetto online did (which is changing like everything to make it different), or you can shut up. That’s your options here.
Personally, I think you should do both.
